## Aspire Integration for Desktop

**DesktopApp.csproj** Configuration:
```xml
<!-- Use Aspire for Orleans silo orchestration -->
<ItemGroup>
    <ProjectReference Include="../Orleans/Orleans.csproj" />
</ItemGroup>
```

**Program.cs**:
```csharp
var host = new HostBuilder()
    .ConfigureServices(services =>
    {
        // Add Orleans silo
        services.AddOrleans((context, siloBuilder) =>
        {
            siloBuilder
                .UseLocalhostClustering()
                .ConfigureApplicationParts(parts =>
                {
                    parts.AddApplicationPart(typeof(ExecutionInstanceGrain).Assembly)
                         .WithReferences();
                })
                .UseDashboard(options =>
                {
                    options.Port = 8080;  // Local dashboard at localhost:8080
                });
        });
        
        // Add desktop-specific services
        services.AddSingleton<MainWindow>();
        services.AddSingleton<DashboardViewModel>();
        services.AddSingleton<IDialogService, WinUIDialogService>();
        services.AddSingleton<IFileService, WinUIFileService>();
    })
    .Build();

// Start Orleans silo
await host.StartAsync();

// Launch desktop app
var mainWindow = host.Services.GetRequiredService<MainWindow>();
mainWindow.Activate();

await host.WaitForShutdownAsync();
```

---

## Build & Deployment: Windows 11 Desktop

### Development: MSIX Package (Local Install)

```bash
# Build desktop app
dotnet publish -c Release -p:WindowsPackageVersion=1.0.0.0

# Output: DesktopApp_1.0.0.0_x64.msix
# Double-click to install on Windows 11
```

### Distribution Options (Phase 3+)

1. **App Installer** (.appinstaller file)
   - Auto-update capability
   - Distributed via corporate file share
   - Users install via .appinstaller file

2. **Microsoft Store** (optional)
   - Public distribution
   - Requires code signing & Store submission
   - Auto-update through Store

3. **Stand-alone .exe**
   - Traditional standalone executable
   - Self-contained .NET runtime (larger file)
   - No Store/MSIX packaging

---

## Performance & Resource Usage

### Desktop Application Targets

| Metric | Target | Notes |
|--------|--------|-------|
| Startup time | < 3 seconds | Orleans silo init + UI render |
| CSV load (3 files) | < 1 second | 150–200 tasks |
| Convergence calculation | < 5 seconds | 150 tasks, 3 rounds avg |
| Timeline render (100 tasks visible) | < 500ms | Canvas or DataGrid|
| Memory usage (idle) | < 200 MB | Orleans + WinUI 3 |
| Memory usage (executing plan) | < 500 MB | 150 tasks + grain states |

### Windows 11 System Requirements

```xml
<!-- Package.appxmanifest -->
<MinimumOS Build="22621" />  <!-- Windows 11 build 22621+ -->
<ProcessorArchitecture>x64</ProcessorArchitecture>
<ProcessorArchitecture>arm64</ProcessorArchitecture>
```

- **RAM**: 4 GB minimum, 8 GB recommended
- **.NET Runtime**: 8.0 or later (bundled with MSIX)
- **Storage**: 150 MB (including .NET runtime)

---

## Security & File Access

### Phase 2 (Single-User Desktop)

- **No authentication** required
- **Local file system access** via File Picker API
- **No network access** (purely local Orleans silo)
- **No data persistence** (memory-only grains, Phase 2)

### Phase 3+ (Corporate Deployment)

- Corporate network file access (SMB/UNC paths)
- Optional: Windows Credential Manager integration
- Optional: Audit logging to network file share
- Optional: Active Directory group policies

---

## Testing Strategy

### Unit Tests (Orleans Grains)

```csharp
[TestClass]
public class ExecutionInstanceGrainTests
{
    private TestSilo _testSilo;
    
    [TestInitialize]
    public async Task Setup()
    {
        _testSilo = new TestSilo();
        await _testSilo.StartAsync();
    }
    
    [TestMethod]
    public async Task CalculateResolvedStartTime_WithPrerequisite_AdjustsStart()
    {
        // Arrange
        var grain = _testSilo.GrainFactory
            .GetGrain<IExecutionInstanceGrain>("Task2_Monday_090000");
        
        // Act
        await grain.InitializeAsync(/* ... */);
        var resolvedStart = await grain.CalculateResolvedStartTimeAsync();
        
        // Assert
        Assert.IsTrue(resolvedStart > expectedMinimum);
    }
}
```

### Integration Tests (Desktop App)

```csharp
[TestClass]
public class TimelineViewTests
{
    [TestMethod]
    public async Task TimelineView_LoadsCsvAndRenders()
    {
        // Load test CSV files
        var taskDefs = Path.Combine(TestData, "tasks.csv");
        var intakeEvents = Path.Combine(TestData, "intake.csv");
        
        // Simulate UI interactions
        var vm = new TimelineViewModel(grainFactory);
        await vm.LoadCsvFilesCommand.ExecuteAsync(new[] { taskDefs, intakeEvents });
        
        // Assert timeline rendered
        Assert.AreEqual(150, vm.ExecutionInstances.Count);
        Assert.IsTrue(vm.ConvergenceProgress.HasConverged);
    }
}
```

### Manual Testing Scenarios

1. **Simple Linear Chain**: Task A → B → C all on Monday
2. **Diamond Dependency**: B & C depend on A; D depends on B & C
3. **Deadline Violation**: Task scheduled too late to meet deadline
4. **Multi-Round Convergence**: Adjustments needed across 3 rounds
5. **CSV Parse Error**: Handle missing/invalid columns gracefully

