## Technology Decisions & Rationale

### 1. Orleans 8.x

**Why Orleans?**
- Virtual actor model ideal for independent task calculations
- Built-in grain persistence and reminders
- Distributed transaction support (not needed here but available)
- Rich monitoring/diagnostics
- Microsoft-backed, production-tested in Azure services

**Key Orleans Packages**:
```xml
<PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Orleans.Server" Version="8.*" />
<PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Orleans.Core" Version="8.*" />
<PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting" Version="8.*" />
<PackageReference Include="OrleansDashboard" Version="8.*" />  <!-- Local dev UI -->
```

**Grain State Persistence** (Phase 2: memory-only, Phase 3+: SQLite/Azure Table Storage):
```csharp
// Phase 2: In-memory state
siloBuilder.UseDashboard(options => { ... })
           .ConfigureApplicationParts(parts => { ... });

// Phase 3: Persistent state
siloBuilder.AddAzureTableGrainStorage("grain-storage", options => { ... });
```

---

### 2. Microsoft Aspire

**Why Aspire?**
- Unified development experience for distributed apps
- ServiceRegistry for inter-service discovery
- Local dashboard showing service health
- Environment variable injection
- Container orchestration abstractions ready

**Key Aspire Packages**:
```xml
<PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Extensions.ServiceDiscovery" Version="8.*" />
<PackageReference Include="Aspire.Hosting" Version="8.*" />
<PackageReference Include="Aspire.Hosting.AppHost" Version="8.*" />
```

**Local Development**:
```bash
dotnet run --project AppHost/AppHost.csproj
# Automatically starts:
# - Orleans silo (localhost:11111)
# - ASP.NET Core API (localhost:5001)
# - React dev server (localhost:5173)
# - Aspire dashboard (localhost:18888)
```

**Production Deployment** (future):
- Azure Container Apps (serverless Kubernetes)
- Kubernetes with Dapr sidecars
- Service Bus for inter-service messaging

---

### 3. ASP.NET Core 8 Web API

**Why ASP.NET Core?**
- Native C# integration with Orleans grains
- High-performance request handling
- Built-in dependency injection
- Structured logging
- OpenAPI/Swagger support

**Architecture**:
```
Controllers
    ├─ ReportsController (GET execution plans)
    ├─ GroupsController (GET group-specific data)
    ├─ TimelineController (GET Gantt chart data)
    └─ DeadlinesController (GET violation reports)
         ↓
Services (business logic)
    └─ GrainClientService (Orleans integration)
         ↓
Orleans Grains (distributed calculation)
```

**Key Packages**:
```xml
<PackageReference Include="Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi" Version="8.*" />
<PackageReference Include="Swashbuckle.AspNetCore" Version="6.*" />  <!-- Swagger UI -->
<PackageReference Include="Orleans.Client" Version="8.*" />
```

**API Response DTOs**:
```csharp
[ApiController]
[Route("api/[controller]")]
public class ReportsController : ControllerBase
{
    [HttpGet("{reportId}")]
    public async Task<ActionResult<ExecutionPlanDto>> GetReport(string reportId)
    {
        // Grain call → JSON response
    }
}
```

---

### 4. React + Vite (Web Frontend)

**Why React?**
- Component-based UI ideal for complex dashboards
- Strong ecosystem (charting, data tables, styling)
- Developer experience (fast hot reload, great TypeScript support)
- Vite provides extremely fast dev server

**Why Vite over Create React App?**
- 10-50x faster dev server startup
- Instant HMR (Hot Module Reload)
- Smaller bundle sizes
- ESM-based, modern tooling

**Architecture**:
```
src/
├─ pages/
│  ├─ Dashboard.tsx
│  ├─ Groups.tsx
│  ├─ Timeline.tsx
│  └─ Violations.tsx
├─ components/
│  ├─ GanttChart.tsx (timeline visualization)
│  ├─ TaskCard.tsx
│  ├─ DeadlineIndicator.tsx
│  └─ ConvergenceProgress.tsx
├─ services/
│  └─ apiClient.ts (HTTP calls to ASP.NET Core)
├─ types/
│  └─ execution-plan.ts (TypeScript interfaces)
└─ App.tsx (routing)
```

